# wsr-pal main_loop.pal - the REAL interactive human-playable loop
# (per direct instruction: human testability above all things). Reads
# keypresses from history.txt (keyboard_input.c writes them),
# dispatches every real key to wsr_menu_input.+x (which internally does
# BOTH digit-accumulation AND Enter-commit, matching mutaclsym's own
# proven title_input.c all-in-one design - simpler than muchi-pal-
# chat's own split buffer_key/send_message shape since there's no
# free-text entry here, only numbered-menu digits), then recomposes and
# hits the frame every tick, matching this whole family's proven
# 3-process (keyboard_input/prisc+x/renderer) shape.
# History cursor is persisted to player_app/state.txt to avoid replaying
# the entire history.txt on process restart (e.g. after a crash).
read_state x1, player_app history_cursor
li x3, 3
li x10, 10
li x13, 13
compose_frame
hit_frame
loop:
read_history x2, x1
beq x2, x0, tick
beq x2, x3, quit
wsr_menu_input x2
update_history_cursor
tick:
compose_frame
hit_frame
sleep 30000
j loop
quit:
halt
